📘 GUIDE 1: FOR PERSON A (UI DESIGNER)
Hey! You're going to make the app look beautiful. Here's exactly what to do.

🚀 STEP 1: Get the Code
Go to the GitHub link your project leader sent

Click the green "Code" button

Click "Download ZIP"

Extract the folder to your Desktop

💻 STEP 2: Open Terminal
Open the extracted folder

Click in the address bar at the top

Type cmd and press Enter

A black window opens - this is your terminal

📦 STEP 3: Install Everything
In the black terminal window, type these commands ONE BY ONE:

text
pip install streamlit
pip install opencv-python
pip install mediapipe
pip install scikit-learn
pip install pandas
pip install numpy
pip install Pillow
Wait for each one to finish before typing the next.

🧪 STEP 4: Test the App
Type this in the terminal:

text
streamlit run app.py
If a browser opens with the app, you're ready to start!

To stop the app: Press Ctrl + C

🎨 STEP 5: Your Tasks
Open app.py in Notepad (right-click → Open with → Notepad)

Task 1: Add a Sidebar
Find this line:

text
st.title("🎨 AI Personal Color Analysis")
Copy and paste this RIGHT AFTER it:

text
with st.sidebar:
    st.markdown("## About This App")
    st.markdown("This AI analyzes your skin undertone")
    st.markdown("---")
    st.markdown("### How to Use")
    st.markdown("1. Upload a photo")
    st.markdown("2. Wait for analysis")
    st.markdown("3. Get recommendations")
    st.markdown("---")
    st.markdown("Made with ❤️ by Team AI")
Task 2: Add Download Button
Scroll to the very bottom of the file. Find this line:

text
st.markdown('</div>', unsafe_allow_html=True)
Copy and paste this RIGHT BEFORE that line:

text
    st.download_button(
        label="Download My Report",
        data=f"Undertone: {prediction}",
        file_name="my_report.txt"
    )
